&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Document&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Table of Contents]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#login&quot;&gt;Log into the SAP website&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#register&quot;&gt;Register at sap.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#activate&quot;&gt;Activate your account&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#logon&quot;&gt;Log on to SAP Cloud Platform&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#verify&quot;&gt;Verify your account&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#access&quot;&gt;Access the welcome screen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;h1 id=&quot;login&quot;&gt;Log into the SAP website&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      Visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sap.com&quot;&gt;https://www.sap.com&lt;/a&gt; and click the
      Log On icon in the upper-right corner.

      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/homepage.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      If you have an account on www.sap.com (e.g. an S, C, D or I number) you
      can enter it or the associated email along with your password. If you
      don’t have an account yet, you can select one of the other login methods
      or click Register to create an account.
      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/option-logon.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;h1 id=&quot;register&quot;&gt;Register at sap.com&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      If you don’t have an account you will see a register dialog on the
      left-hand side of the dialog. Fill in the required fields, and click
      Submit.
      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/option-register.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
      You will get a message that an activation link has been sent to you.
      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/register_confirm.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;h2 id=&quot;activate&quot;&gt;Activate your account&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      Check your emails to find the activation button Click to activate your
      account.
      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/log-into-sap.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;

      After activating your account, you will see the following screen
      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/successful-activation.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;h1 id=&quot;logon&quot;&gt;Log on to SAP Cloud Platform&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      After activation, or if you already had an SAP account, go to the
      &lt;a href=&quot;https://account.hanatrial.ondemand.com/&quot;
        &gt;SAP Cloud Platform Trial&lt;/a
      &gt;
      page and click &lt;b&gt;Log On&lt;/b&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;
      You will see an dialog to confirm the terms and condition for the SAP
      Cloud Platform Developer Edition. Check the check boxes and click
      &lt;b&gt;Accept&lt;/b&gt;. This simply adds the SAP.com registration to your login
      account on SAP Cloud Identity. There is no cost associated with this
      upgrade

      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/legal-disclaimer.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;h1 id=&quot;verify&quot;&gt;Verify your account&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      You will see a message that you need to verify your account with a phone
      number. Click Verify your phone number to trigger that flow.
      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/verification.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
      &lt;br /&gt;
      Enter your phone number and click New Code to retrieve a code. Please
      enter this code as well and click Continue to verify your account. After
      the verification, you will be logged off automatically

      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/number.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;h1 id=&quot;access&quot;&gt;Access the welcome screen&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      Click on Log on to log on to your verified account.
      &lt;img
        src=&quot;https://developers.sap.com/tutorials/hcp-create-trial-account/_jcr_content.github-proxy.1594886410.file/logon-again.png&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
      You will see one main button on the welcome screen of the SAP Cloud
      Platform Cockpit. Click on Enter Your Trial Account to navigate to your
      global account.

      &lt;img
        src=&quot;/New-Tech-Reference-Blog/img/ContentRelated/SAPCPTrial/CreateAccount.gif&quot;
        alt=&quot;&quot;
      /&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html">Document [Table of Contents] Log into the SAP website Register at sap.com Activate your account Log on to SAP Cloud Platform Verify your account Access the welcome screen Log into the SAP website Visit https://www.sap.com and click the Log On icon in the upper-right corner.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">API Testing via postman</title><link href="/New-Tech-Reference-Blog/2020/10/05/APITestingViaPostman.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="API Testing via postman" /><published>2020-10-05T00:00:00+05:30</published><updated>2020-10-05T00:00:00+05:30</updated><id>/New-Tech-Reference-Blog/2020/10/05/APITestingViaPostman</id><content type="html" xml:base="/New-Tech-Reference-Blog/2020/10/05/APITestingViaPostman.html">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Document&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
      pre {
        background-color: #f8f8f8;
        border: 1px solid #cccccc;
        border-radius: 3px;
        overflow-x: auto;
        white-space: pre-wrap;
        overflow-wrap: break-word;
